    {
      "id": "f495f532_32232aab",
      "file_path": "models-base/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/models/base/PfConceptContainer.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 79,
      "message": "the annotations defined in policy/common (e.g., NotNull) are modeled after those on javax.validation, thus I don't think they should be changed.  However, those defined in policy/models (e.g., Key) are specific to policy, thus I'm open to renaming them.\n\nquestion: should @VerifyKey also imply @Valid (i.e., invoke the key.validated() method)?  If not, then I'll need to add @Valid to most of the places where @Key is currently used.",
